# Design System Architecture

LexMastery uses a centralized Design System.

Every visual element must originate from the Design System.

Never design individual screens independently.

Every screen belongs to one visual language.

---

# Design Philosophy

LexMastery is

Professional

Elegant

Academic

Editorial

Calm

Minimal

Modern

Premium

Trustworthy

Focused

Never create playful interfaces.

Never create gaming interfaces.

Never create social media interfaces.

The application should feel like

Notion

Linear

Stripe Dashboard

Apple Books

Headway

—not—

TikTok

Instagram

Duolingo

---

# Design Principles

Every interface should

Reduce cognitive load

Increase confidence

Guide attention

Communicate hierarchy

Promote focus

Minimize distractions

Support long study sessions

Never overwhelm users.

---

# Design Layers

Every UI element originates from

Design Tokens

↓

Theme

↓

Foundation Components

↓

Composite Components

↓

Screen Patterns

↓

Screens

Never skip layers.

---

# Design Tokens

The Design Token layer owns

Colors

Typography

Spacing

Radius

Elevation

Borders

Motion

Opacity

Sizing

Icons

Tokens are the single source of truth.

Never hardcode values.

---

# Theme Layer

The Theme layer converts tokens into Flutter themes.

Examples

ThemeData

ColorScheme

TextTheme

ThemeExtensions

Never hardcode theme values inside Widgets.

---

# Foundation Components

Foundation components are primitive building blocks.

Examples

Button

Text

Input

Icon

Avatar

Divider

Badge

Chip

Switch

Checkbox

Radio

Progress

These should be highly reusable.

---

# Composite Components

Composite components combine primitives.

Examples

Course Card

Lesson Tile

Question Card

Progress Card

Study Session Card

Legal Citation Card

AI Message Bubble

AI Suggestion Card

Flashcard

Quiz Summary

Performance Graph

Composite components belong in Shared only after proven reuse.

---

# Screen Patterns

A screen is assembled from

Layouts

↓

Sections

↓

Composite Components

↓

Foundation Components

Never build screens directly from primitives.

---

# Visual Hierarchy

Every screen should have

Primary Content

↓

Secondary Content

↓

Supporting Content

↓

Metadata

↓

Actions

Hierarchy should be immediately obvious.

---

# Spacing Rhythm

Spacing must feel intentional.

Whitespace is a design element.

Never compress content unnecessarily.

Never create uneven spacing.

Spacing comes only from Design Tokens.

---

# Typography Rhythm

Typography establishes hierarchy.

Headings

↓

Subheadings

↓

Body

↓

Supporting Text

↓

Captions

Never invent font sizes.

Always use typography tokens.

---

# Component Consistency

Buttons should always behave the same.

Inputs should always behave the same.

Cards should always behave the same.

Dialogs should always behave the same.

Navigation should always behave the same.

Consistency builds trust.

---

# Motion Philosophy

Motion communicates state.

Never animate for decoration.

Animations should

Guide attention

Confirm actions

Reduce uncertainty

Improve continuity

Motion should feel calm.

---

# Color Philosophy

Color communicates meaning.

Not decoration.

Use color sparingly.

Primary

↓

Information

↓

Success

↓

Warning

↓

Danger

↓

Disabled

Avoid unnecessary accent colors.

---

# Elevation

Elevation indicates interaction.

Higher elevation

↓

Higher importance.

Avoid excessive shadows.

Prefer subtle depth.

---

# Icons

Icons support text.

Never replace text with icons alone.

Icons should remain simple.

Consistent stroke weight.

Consistent sizing.

---

# Accessibility

Every component must support

Large fonts

Screen readers

Reduced motion

High contrast

Touch targets

Accessibility is part of the Design System.

---

# Empty States

Every empty state should

Explain

Educate

Guide

Encourage

Never show blank pages.

---

# Loading States

Every asynchronous component requires

Skeleton

↓

Progress Indicator

↓

Content

Never display empty white screens.

---

# Error States

Errors should be

Clear

Calm

Actionable

Helpful

Never blame the user.

---

# Responsive Design

Design mobile-first.

Scale to tablets.

Maintain rhythm across devices.

Respect safe areas.

---

# Cursor Instructions

Before creating any UI:

Determine existing component.

Determine screen pattern.

Determine spacing.

Determine typography.

Determine motion.

Determine accessibility.

Only then build the interface.

Never invent new visual styles.

Always extend the Design System.